Vice President Joe Biden met with Czech Prime Minister Bohuslav Sobotka to discuss bilateral relations, the crisis in Ukraine, and European energy security. Biden expressed appreciation for the Czech Republic's contributions to international security and emphasized the importance of strengthening the NATO Alliance. He also highlighted the need for allies to reinvest in defense and share the cost of security. Biden underscored the importance of imposing costs on Russia for its violations of Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity, as well as its disregard for commitments made in the Minsk agreement. The leaders also agreed on the importance of enhancing Europe's energy security and creating a true market for natural gas. Lastly, Biden expressed admiration for the late Czech President Vaclav Havel and his legacy as a champion for human rights.